Weekend Update: 05/26/19

Guys, I am no longer wearing matching braces with my tweenagers! I’m officially braces-free and am celebrating by eating my way through gummy candies. After 14 months, I was ready to be done!

I have been so happy with the results and am honestly super happy that I did them. I was in a fairly bad car accident years ago that resulted in some heavy surgery and scarring in my jaw, so to be able to finally bite right, have my teeth aligned, and have full mobility again is life-changing.

For those of you on the fence about getting braces as an adult, it’s one of the best decisions I have made. And if you don’t think you’ll survive, don’t worry, I put together this fail-proof survival guide all about adult braces just for you!

Emery Is Junior High Bound!

Oh man, I’m not ready to have a middle schooler! Emery graduated from Elementary school (and got a picture with the boy who gave her a 4 out of 3 during the school talent show).

Teenagers and boyfriends are so not something I’m ready for!

EMERY’S SHOES | MY SHOES | MY JEANS | BRAUN’S SHOES

She did, however, get an award for being the most athletic in her 6th-grade class. She beat out all the boys by doing 32 pull-ups and ran her mile in 7 minutes and 27 seconds…which means that 6th-grade boys are in awe of her and she beat me by about 30 seconds on my most recent mile run soooo, I owe her some cold hard cash.

I’m working on making bets I know are a sure thing!

Other than Emery growing up way too fast, she continues to be a bright light in the Thueson household. Gosh, I love this girl. She makes this whole mom-job easy!

JETT’S SHOES

We have another graduate in the house who gets 2 more years of it though due to his September birthday! Jett graduated his first year of preschool and Braun and I attended his graduation where he sang a lot of songs and at the end of each of them would yell “THANK YOU… THANK YOU… SOOOOO MUCH!” This kid does not lack enthusiasm!

I see this big grin and forget about all the times he makes me crazy…and then he brings me a piece of his poop in his hand and I’m quickly reminded of what an adventure he is! Haha

Memorial Day Weekend Getaway

We came up to our friends’ cabin this weekend for Memorial Day, and it’s so nice to get away! I slept in until 11 am yesterday AND got a nap in. And I don’t even feel bad – haha! The kids have been out getting dirty as can be and I have been trying to organize my computer and phone. It’s a never-ending battle to organize my life/work/mom/church/work shtuff.

We made sure to bring all of our beading supplies (you can see what we have HERE and grab your own) for the girls to make bracelets, a few games which I’ll link below and my friend stopped at the dollar store on the way up and grabbed a whole bunch of painting supplies – SUPER SMART! These types of purchases always end up being the BEST! The kids are loving them so if you need a cheap summer activity, go to the dollar store and stock up!

Games We Play

#1 Cover Your Assets – always #1. Dash wants to play this every chance he gets. P.S. I also just got a massive box of games from the same company AND a brand new one they’re launching and I can’t wait to share it with you guys!!!

#2 Qwirkle – a game we always love!

#3 Q-Bitz – we got this recently and it is a good brain activity! It is kind of tough for Dash who is 7 but he is getting better at it every time and he likes the challenge.

#4- Tenzi – We LOVE this game. You can play it with a ton of people (they just each have to have their own color of dice) When we play with my big family, we use THIS set of dice and THIS set of dice plus you’ve got to have the deck of cards.

#5 NERTZ – a classic!

All of these games are super easy to travel with so they get played a lot.
